      <div class="space-y-4 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="collapse collapse-plus bg-base-200 rounded-2xl">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" checked="checked" /> 
          <div class="collapse-title text-xl font-bold p-6">
            How is interest calculated on a construction loan?
          </div>
          <div class="collapse-content px-6 pb-6"> 
            <p class="opacity-80 leading-relaxed">Interest is typically calculated only on the disbursed amount (the 'draws'), not the total loan commitment. As you draw more funds to pay subcontractors and material costs, your monthly interest payments increase proportionally. This interest-only period generally lasts for the duration of the build phase.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="collapse collapse-plus bg-base-200 rounded-2xl">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" /> 
          <div class="collapse-title text-xl font-bold p-6">
            What is a draw schedule?
          </div>
          <div class="collapse-content px-6 pb-6"> 
            <p class="opacity-80 leading-relaxed">A draw schedule is a detailed timeline of when project funds will be released by the lender. These releases are triggered by the completion of specific construction milestones (e.g., foundation complete, framing complete), verified by a third-party inspector to ensure the funds match the value of work in place.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="collapse collapse-plus bg-base-200 rounded-2xl">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" /> 
          <div class="collapse-title text-xl font-bold p-6">
            How do carry costs affect my project margin?
          </div>
          <div class="collapse-content px-6 pb-6"> 
            <p class="opacity-80 leading-relaxed">Carry costs, primarily loan interest and property taxes, eat directly into your net profit. Unlike hard costs (bricks and mortar), carry costs are "waste" costs that expand when projects are delayed. Without precision tracking, these costs can silently consume your entire project contingency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
